Another contradiction of the same nature, is this, That the manifestation of the spirit is given (to no man for himself, bu
                        •
                     ) to every man to profit withal, to edifie, and build up, and do service in the body, as an hand, foot or eye, or some other member of the body &c. and to contradict this, in the next words he saith, Not that the spirit, or the manifestation of the spirit is given to every man (i e.) to every individual person forasmuch as some men are sensual, having not the spirit, therefore no manefestation thereof, pag, 17.
